Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteIntegRouteConstraint(25.10)            deleteIntegRouteConstraint(25.10)

Name
       deleteIntegRouteConstraint  -  Deletes  the  routing constraints in the
       database

Syntax
       deleteIntegRouteConstraint

       [-help]

       {-net <net1 net2 ...> | -name <string> | -customConstraints  | -all   |
       -additional }

       Deletes the routing constraints in the database.

       Note: Integration constraints are used to convey the design intent in a
       mixed  signal design. These constraints are fully interoperable between
       the digital and custom environments.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each deleteIntegRouteConstraint parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man deleteIntegRouteConstraint.

       -additional
              Removes  the  additional constraint file, containing the maximum
              resistance target values for nets, from memory.

       -all   Deletes all integration constraints, including constraints  that
              are  understood  by NanoRoute and used to route nets with simple
              shield or NDR constraints.

       -customConstraints
              Deletes all diffPair, matchLength, complex shield,  and  complex
              netClass constraints.

       -name <string>
              Allows  the  deletion  of a specific constraint by name. You can
              specify multiple constraint names, enclosed in braces.  Use  the
              getIntegRouteConstraint  command  to  get  the  name of any con-
              straint in the design.

       -net <net1 net2 ...>
              Indicates the nets for which the constraints will be deleted. If
              the net is part of a netClass, the netClass will be  deleted  as
              well.

Example
              * The  following command deletes all diffPair, matchLength, com-
                plex shield, and complex netClass constraints.

                deleteIntegRouteConstraint -customConstraints

              * The following command deletes the constraints with the  speci-
                fied names:

                deleteIntegRouteConstraint             -name             {Con-
                str_2__analogNW__DTMF_INST/analogNW_INST                  Con-
                str_1__analogNW__DTMF_INST/analogNW_INST}

              * The  following  command deletes all Integration constraints in
                the design.

                deleteIntegRouteConstraint -all

                The tool displays the following warning  before  deleting  the
                constraints:

                **WARN:  (IMPOAX-2237): You are attempting to delete all rout-
                ing constraints in this design. These include many constraints
                that are intended for use by NR for routing nets  with  simple
                shield, or NDR constraints.

